'''46度暈'''是一種很罕見的出現在[[太陽|太陽]]附近的[[暈|暈]]。當太陽與水平線的夾角呈15-27°時，46度暈很容易與[[上側弧|上側弧]]與[[外側弧|外側弧]]混淆。<ref>The 46° halo was first explained as being caused by refractions through ice crystals in 1679 by the French physicist [[Edme_Mariotte|Edmé Mariotte]] (1620–1684).  See:  Mariotte, ''Quatrieme Essay.  De la Nature des Couleur'' (Paris, France:  Estienne Michallet, 1681).  Sun dogs as well as the 22° and 46° halos are explained in terms of refractions from ice crystals on [http://books.google.com/books?id=y10O12JjHskC&pg=PA466#v=onepage&q&f=false pages 466 - 524] {{Wayback|url=http://books.google.com/books?id=y10O12JjHskC&pg=PA466#v=onepage&q&f=false |date=20200806035434 }}.</ref>

